Sentencas: We demonstrate the utilization of bismuth tungstate (Bi2WO6, BW) as a sintering aid and reinforcement component into neodymium-doped ceria (Nd0.2Ce0.8O3.delta, NDC) to fabricate bismuth tungstate/neodymiumdoped ceria composite electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Bismuth tungstate/neodymium-doped ceria composite electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Sintering aid and composite effect

Sentencas: The presence of BW lowers the sintering temperature of NDC electrolyte to 1000 degrees C. Moreover, at 600 degrees C, the electrical conductivity of 5 mol.% BW-incorporated NDC (5BW-NDC) composite electrolyte is 7.12 times higher than the NDC.
Titulo: Bismuth tungstate/neodymium-doped ceria composite electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Sintering aid and composite effect

Sentencas: It is worth mentioning that the enhanced electrical conductivity of 5BW-NDC composite electrolyte does not include the contribution from electronic conductivity.
Titulo: Bismuth tungstate/neodymium-doped ceria composite electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Sintering aid and composite effect

Sentencas: Furthermore, NDC and 5BW-NDC exhibit excellent compatibility with La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3.delta cathode and NiO anode in terms of thermal expansion coefficient and chemical reactivity.
Titulo: Bismuth tungstate/neodymium-doped ceria composite electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Sintering aid and composite effect

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction reaction at 5BW-NDC composite electrolyte/cathode interface is significantly enhanced by similar to 40% compared to NDC.
Titulo: Bismuth tungstate/neodymium-doped ceria composite electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Sintering aid and composite effect

Sentencas: Moreover, 5BW-NDC electrolyte-supported SOFC delivers a power density of 0.86 W cm(-2) at 700 degrees C, which is 45.76% higher than the NDC-based SOFC.
Titulo: Bismuth tungstate/neodymium-doped ceria composite electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Sintering aid and composite effect

Sentencas: The output performance remains stable during high-temperature operation for 120 h, which indicates the stability and chemical compatibility of the as-synthesized composite electrolyte with other cell components.
Titulo: Bismuth tungstate/neodymium-doped ceria composite electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Sintering aid and composite effect

Sentencas: The results reveal that BW-NDC composite is a potential electrolyte material for stable and high-performance IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Bismuth tungstate/neodymium-doped ceria composite electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Sintering aid and composite effect
